            <thetext>The inspector usually adapts to the browser width, e.g. by putting toolbar 
controls in an overflow menu. When loading the app to inspect (&quot;AUT&quot;), new 
controls are being added (e.g. a &quot;qx.ui.root.Application ..&quot; label). But this 
pushes the overflow menu out of the viewport, without any hint or possibility 
to access it. A subsequent resize of the window, even minimal, triggers a 
recalculation and all controls are accessible again.</thetext>
